    {
      "id": "5a93c517_c6310fa3",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/nbi/requirements.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 22,
      "message": "It is really great that you are making use of the stable helm charts.  And as a longer term goal we may want to do more of this. For now, I would recommend reusing the embedded mariadb chart (see champ/charts/mariadb) instead of pulling the stable version. This sets the stage for use to move towards databases-as-a-service in the Casablanca timeframe. In addition you will get standardized/centralized configuration, and swappable PV/PVC/StorageClasses (coming soon).\n\nFor mongodb, it would be good to pull the stable version you are referencing, and default PV & PVC descriptors (use mariadb as a guide) and drop it into common/mongodb. This will be along side the other common db charts like mysql, postgres, mariadb-galera.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 127,
        "name": "Mike Elliott",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "mike.elliott@amdocs.com",
        "username": "melliott"
