    {
      "id": "5a93c517_46e41f0c",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/onap/requirements.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 83,
      "message": "I believe that import-values allows you to pull configuration from sub charts of the parent chart (nbi in this case) into the parent chart. I don't think you can grab config from a chart that is at the same level within the onap umbrella chart. \nThere is a way to share common configuration between onap charts that involves templating a set of configuration (eg. Openstack params) and referencing them in sub charts like so, nbi and robot (where they are needed). Ping myself or Mandeep and we can guide you on this change. For now, just duplicate the config you need from so to get it working.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 127,
        "name": "Mike Elliott",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "mike.elliott@amdocs.com",
        "username": "melliott"
